caption.text:
Have you ever wondered what “Green Entrepreneurship” really means?🌱 

Maybe the first things that came to mind were planting trees, recycling, or working directly with nature. Or maybe you thought it’s only for those who want to “save the world”… or that it’s less profitable than traditional businesses.

But let’s take a step back…
It’s not just a “green image,” but real solutions to the problems created by today’s extractive and polluting economic systems.

In the second episode of the Green Entrepreneurship Series with Najlaa Abdellatif, founder of Zero Waste Palestine, we dive into what green entrepreneurship truly is, explore innovative business models, and discover inspiring examples of Palestinian startups.

And if you also want to learn about the risks of “greenwashing” and how to distinguish real environmental entrepreneurship from misleading marketing, watch Episode 2 now on YouTube and see how you can be part of the solution!

🔗 Watch the full episode on our YouTube channel.

The Green Forward programme is funded by the European Union and is implemented at the meso level by SPARK and Flow Accelerator in Palestine to foster a green and circular economy (GCE) in the Southern Neighbourhood region.
